Disrupt.sh is an application launcher which will launch an application at a set interval constantly. Application is set to be code in this instance.

Off.sh is a script written to turn your device off in a set time. Set the hour you want to turn your device off in timer variable and set the minute in the condition variable.

Open.sh is a script written to mitigate having to update and upgrade your linux system in daily basis. You can put this file into /etc/rc6.d/ as K99_filename without any extension and it should run while you open your device.


Additionally, you need to provide permission to all the shell scripts in order for them to execute.
You can do this with,
chmod +x scriptname.sh

:) have a Good day.
